{
  "summary": "In Seattle's soaring housing market, Bud Dodson and John Warden have converted vehicles into affordable homes. Living in the SoDo district's parking lot, their stories are captured in a vivid photographic series by Anna Erickson. Their capsule homes, like Worden's $200 car, act as mobile residences. Working as a panhandler at Safeco Field stadium, Warden is content in his unique lifestyle. This unconventional solution provides a microcosm of innovation amidst housing crises."
}

{
  "summary": "Jonathan Maitland's forthcoming play, 'An Audience with Jimmy Savile', stars Alistair McGowan as Savile. It portrays Savile's disgraced life and the societal aftermath, sourcing from actual events and responses. Set for a London launch in June, less than three years post documentary unveiling Savile's depravity, it nudges wider cultural discourse."
}

{
  "summary": "Mamadou Sakho sustained a hamstring injury during Liverpool's 1-0 FA Cup replay victory against Blackburn Rovers at Ewood Park, propelling Brendan Rodgers to rely on remaining defenders, Kolo Toure and Dejan Lovren. Rodgers, needing to cover the one match ban of Emre Can and ongoing absence of Martin Skrtel, awaits a swift Sakho recovery while preparing for the next Premier League face-off with Newcastle United."
}

{
  "summary": "Post Chinese Grand Prix, escalating tension between Lewis Hamilton and Nico Rosberg evident on their Emirates flight to Dubai and public disputes. Disagreements emerge regarding different racing strategies, with Hamilton facing allegations of race tampering. Mercedes directors, Toto Wolff and Paddy Lowe, mediate while third-placed Sebastian Vettel lurks in the fray. Discord continues in Shanghai paddock before the next race."
}

{
  "summary": "World champion Charlotte Dujardin and her horse, Valegro, secured the Grand Prix title at the Las Vegas World Cup, besting runners-up Edward Gal and Steffen Peters. Despite not replicating her record score from Lyon and initial worries about Valegro's health, Dujardin's satisfaction with her performance remained undiminished."
}

{
  "summary": "An 'Apple promo' vintage Quartz watch from the 90s, minus any digital or phone capabilities, lists for high values on eBay, matching prices of advanced Apple products. Promoting the Mac OS, it's considered a rare 'collector's item' by seller 'theappleipodbay'. Its nondigital screen with Apple's old rainbow logo contrasts starkly with the costly Apple Watch Sport and Apple Watch Edition. Further discussion on recent Apple watches is briefly touched upon."
}

{
  "summary": "Douglas Bader, a legless British fighter ace, led an audacious WW2 prison escape codenamed Operation Olympian, prior to the renowned Great Escape. Folding ladders were crafted covertly in a music room, becoming part of the cinematic and literary history. These feats will be revisited in an upcoming Hollywood film, 'The First Great Escape', based on Dr Felton’s book, produced by Essential 11 USA."
}

{
  "summary": "Four Seasons expands its lavish hospitality to the skies, offering one-of-a-kind, around the world journey with its private jet, designed by Italian Iacobucci, brimming with high-class amenities including gourmet meals and Dom Pérignon champagne. Priced at approximately £63,000 a trip, it mirrors the hotel's grandeur while also available for private charter despite its opulent cost."
}

{
  "summary": "Kent Sprouse, sentenced to death in Texas in 2004, confessed to the 2002 murders of Officer Steinfeldt and Pedro Moreno. Lawyers Jim Jenkins and Don Maxfield, and Ferris Police Chief Sam Love evaluate Sprouse's mental health during his failed appeals. His impending execution by lethal injection, a challenge considering advocacy against capital punishment, sustains Texas' stand on death penalty."
}

{
  "summary": "Famed designer, Collette Dinnigan moves from her lovingly restored 19th-century Paddington home, listed by Ben Collier of McGrath Estate Agents. James Packer's confidant Matthew Csidei's former Masonic Lodge is Dinnigan's $6.5m Watson Bay home bought with husband Bradley Cocks. Her property dealings in Sydney's bourgeois areas, merging with her celebrated fashion career, and evolving residential needs are scrutinized."
}

{
  "summary": "Michael Carrick, Manchester United's key player, outperforms legends like Sir Bobby Charlton, David Beckham, and Gary Lineker, aiming to surpass Sir Stanley Matthews as England's longest-serving outfield player. Applauded by Wayne Rooney for his virtuoso performance against Italy, Carrick is on track to overtake Peter Shilton, Steven Gerrard, and Frank Lampard if he extends to Euro 2016."
}

{
  "summary": "The Champions League could bring a third El Clasico showdown between Real Madrid and Barcelona this season. Powerful players Neymar, Javier Hernandez, Cristiano Ronaldo, and Lionel Messi are anticipated for an exceptional display of skill. With a record global audience expected, this duel underscores their enduring rivalry and remarkable history."
}

{
  "summary": "Judged by the Menu Innovation and Development Awards (MIDAS), Morrisons supermarket clinched Britain's Best Breakfast, toppling rival entities like Marriott, Wetherspoons, Bella Italia, and it's predecessor, Intercontinental Hotels. Key to the victory was a variety of options from granola to Big Breakfast, championed by head chef Richard Jones for superior food quality, customer satisfaction, and value. Accolade organizer, Inside Foodservice, lauded the triumph and Morrisons' elevated national stature, underscoring the industry prestige."
}

{
  "summary": "21-year-old Jordan Spieth is leading the Masters at Augusta, with potential to shatter Tiger Woods' records and secure a $1.8 million prize. Facing adversaries as Justin Rose, Dustin Johnson, and Phil Mickelson, and personal stakes riding high with girlfriend Annie Verret cheering from Dallas, Texas, Spieth navigates last year's misstep and Woods' suspected health condition unfolding amid the tournament saga. The temperance portrayed by his autistic sister, Ellie, bolsters his performance."
}

{
  "summary": "Endurance-swimming in the frosty North Sea inspired a profound sense of liberation in a non-athlete. The societal history of swimming, including attire mandates, and input from icons like Byron further bolster her tale. She savors the tranquility of Hampstead Heath Ponds and Scotland's untamed beauty. With insights from Freud and Jane Austen, and the thrill akin to watching Poldark, swimming remains a balm despite initial struggles."
}

{
  "summary": "In a televised debate, Nigel Farage blamed UK's problems on immigration, eliciting boos from a BBC audience, selected by Pollster ICM, deemed left-leaning by Farage. His comments were opposed by Ed Miliband, Nicola Sturgeon, and Natalie Bennett, leading a Ukip voter to reconsider their support."
}

{
  "summary": "As Sunderland readies for a potent clash against North-East adversaries Newcastle, chiefs Dick Advocaat and Paul Bracewell refuse to minimize the historic rivalry, reflecting on a previous error in Advocaat's Rangers spell involving Rod Wallace. Amid Adam Johnson's participation uncertainty, recently arrested, the team's league position near relegation amplifies the stakes. The approaching game stirs heightened emotions and anticipation."
}

{
  "summary": "Barcelona's Pedro, sidelined under Luis Enrique due to the Messi, Suarez, Neymar trio, confirms discussion of leaving due to reduced playtime—only 12 league starts. He confesses to Spain’s Al Primer Toque, it's normal in such circumstances. Pedro's focus: maintain composure, assist the team, despite challenges like Jetro Willems on the field. No decision is final yet."
}

{
  "summary": "In Hyde Park, during the global '420' event, 53 pro-cannabis protestors were arrested, highlighting cannabis possession's illegality and advocating for legalization. Main organizers were NORML UK and UKCSC. The event, happening worldwide annually, sharpens the contentious drug legislation debate."
}
